(220, 1, '2018-12-07 23:24:50', '2018-12-08 04:24:50', '<h2>Personal Logo</h2>		\n		<p>Since I was young, I have loved art, computers and space. I am enthralled by the way a brush and some colour can change the look and feel of something. I am astounded by the way you can create something from your mind with a little imagination and some supplies. I have been using a computer since the age of 5 and within a few months, I was teaching my parents how to do things on the computer. And I am completely taken aback by the vastness of space, and imagining what could be out there.</p><p>So, with all these things in mind, a graphic designer seemed like the career that contained the perfect combination of my favourite things and my skill sets. But, where could I introduce some space vibes? Of course, every client wouldn\'t want NASA type logos or galaxy watercolored backgrounds and all that stuff. </p><p>I decided that for my personal logo - I would create a nerdy, spacey, astronaut feel. </p><p>Why not? It\'s my logo!</p>		\n			<h2>The Logo</h2>		\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"433\" height=\"432\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black-100x100.png 100w\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n		<p>This is the basic logo. The logo that would be seen most of the time - you know, when some would say it\'s \"inappropriate\" to have a bright pink logo present. Which is strange... Because pink is a fantastically happy colour. </p>		\n			<h2>Logo Variations</h2>		\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blue.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox