(262, 1, '2018-12-13 16:33:54', '2018-12-13 21:33:54', '<h2>Visual Brand Identity Project</h2>		\n		<p>We were asked to imagine a fictional company located in Central/North Vancouver Island. The project is broken down into five parts: The Strategy, Logo, Stationery, Advert and Landing Page. </p>		\n			<h2>The Logo</h2>		\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"1303\" height=\"508\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED.png\" alt=\"Espress Yourself Logo\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED.png 1303w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED-300x117.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED-768x299.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED-1024x399.png 1024w\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"1300\" height=\"416\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR.png\" alt=\"Espress Yourself Logo Black\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR.png 1300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR-300x96.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR-768x246.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR-1024x328.png 1024w\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n		<p>The logo I created for Espress Yourself incorporates an icon and a wordmark. The icon is a line drawing of a coffee mug with a paint splatter emerging from the top - like coffee spilling out. The font chosen in a brushy-script font called The Historia Demo. \"The Creative Cafe\" font is Mr Eaves XL Mod Nar OT. I chose to include the tagline to better explain the cafe from an outsiders perspective. I kept the colour palette simple by using a dark brown and a bright purple. </p>		\n			<h2>Strategy</h2>		\n		<p> </p><p>Espress Yourself is a self-serve espresso/coffee bar. The client can choose from variety of coffee flavours and prepare their own beverage. The unique aspect of Espress Yourself is it affords the client a chance to contribute to the shop’s atmosphere by providing the means for them to create their own temporary artwork on the walls of the shop.</p><p> The target customers are students, young adults and members of the art community who live in the north Vancouver Island area. They earn a modest or minimum wage. They are creative people such as artists, photographers, designers, etc. What sets this target customer group apart is that they are especially creative. Their perspective on life is flexible and they enjoy having the opportunity to share ideas. In addition, these type of people would benefit from having a place to go where they can perhaps gain inspiration for current or future projects. </p><p><b>Positioning Statement<br /></b><b><br /></b>For [students, young adults and members of the art community], [Espress Yourself] is the [coffee shop] that delivers [a self-serve coffee bar that gives the client the opportunity to create their own coffee beverages and contribute the atmosphere of the shop] because only [Espress Yourself] provides [a fresh canvas not only on the walls but in your favourite mug]. </p><p> </p>		\n			<h2>Stationery</h2>		\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup.png\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Stationery Mockup\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup.png 1920w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup-300x169.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup-768x432.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup-1024x576.png 1024w\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n		<p>The watercolour design on the stationery was hand painted and then scanned in and photoshopped to remove any shadows. I chose to watercolour with browns, purples and some blues to add depth and keep the colour palette consistent. I wanted the watercolour design to look as though it was a mix of paint and coffee spilling out over the page. </p><p>I used this watercolour design on each piece of stationery to keep consistency and an element of fun. I created each piece of stationery using Adobe Illustrator. Once I had finished each piece, I printed them out. I hand-folded and glued the envelope together so it was usable. I made the inside of the envelope a full watercolour design. </p>		\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BusinessCard.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"253\" height=\"145\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BusinessCard.png\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Business Card\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-2.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"253\" height=\"145\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-2.png\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Business Card\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n			<h2>Advert</h2>		\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"612\" height=\"792\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert.png\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Advert\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert.png 612w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert-232x300.png 232w\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n		<p>The advert created is a 8.5X11\" poster printed on card stock. I created the design for this poster on Adobe InDesign. I found the image of the paint roller on a free stock-image website. I came up with the message \"Come. Create. Caffeinate.\" as a simple but effective message to explain what Espress Yourself offers. I added the coffee ring at the bottom because I felt as though the paint roller was not sending the full message visually. </p>		\n			<h2>Landing Page</h2>		\n											<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\n							<img width=\"391\" height=\"709\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE.png\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Landing Page\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE.png 391w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE-165x300.png 165w\" sizes=\"100vw\" />								</a>\n		<p>This landing page for Espress Yourself was designed to motivate the customer to submit their email address and sign up to book their wall space to create on. I wanted to keep the design minimal with a lot of white space. I used images revolving around paint and coffee to keep the landing page on brand. I used the dark brown and bright purple colours for consistency. This landing page consists of a form at the top, the benefits and features section, the testimonial section, and a second call to action at the bottom along with the logo and social media links. </p>', 'Visual Identity Project', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-13 16:33:54', '2018-12-13 21:33:54', '', 9, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/12/13/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
