(269, 1, '2018-12-13 16:46:47', '2018-12-13 21:46:47', '<h2>Visual Brand Identity Project</h2>\r\nWe were asked to imagine a fictional company located in Central/North Vancouver Island. The project is broken down into five parts: The Strategy, Logo, Stationery, Advert and Landing Page.\r\n<h2>The Logo</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED.png 1303w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED-300x117.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED-768x299.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGCOLOURED-1024x399.png 1024w\" alt=\"Espress Yourself Logo\" width=\"1303\" height=\"508\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR.png 1300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR-300x96.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR-768x246.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BIGNOCOLOUR-1024x328.png 1024w\" alt=\"Espress Yourself Logo Black\" width=\"1300\" height=\"416\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe logo I created for Espress Yourself incorporates an icon and a wordmark. The icon is a line drawing of a coffee mug with a paint splatter emerging from the top - like coffee spilling out. The font chosen in a brushy-script font called The Historia Demo. \"The Creative Cafe\" font is Mr Eaves XL Mod Nar OT. I chose to include the tagline to better explain the cafe from an outsiders perspective. I kept the colour palette simple by using a dark brown and a bright purple.\r\n<h2>Strategy</h2>\r\nEspress Yourself is a self-serve espresso/coffee bar. The client can choose from variety of coffee flavours and prepare their own beverage. The unique aspect of Espress Yourself is it affords the client a chance to contribute to the shop’s atmosphere by providing the means for them to create their own temporary artwork on the walls of the shop.\r\n\r\nThe target customers are students, young adults and members of the art community who live in the north Vancouver Island area. They earn a modest or minimum wage. They are creative people such as artists, photographers, designers, etc. What sets this target customer group apart is that they are especially creative. Their perspective on life is flexible and they enjoy having the opportunity to share ideas. In addition, these type of people would benefit from having a place to go where they can perhaps gain inspiration for current or future projects.\r\n\r\n<b>Positioning Statement\r\n</b><b>\r\n</b>For [students, young adults and members of the art community], [Espress Yourself] is the [coffee shop] that delivers [a self-serve coffee bar that gives the client the opportunity to create their own coffee beverages and contribute the atmosphere of the shop] because only [Espress Yourself] provides [a fresh canvas not only on the walls but in your favourite mug].\r\n<h2>Stationery</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup.png 1920w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup-300x169.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup-768x432.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaStationeryMockup-1024x576.png 1024w\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Stationery Mockup\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe watercolour design on the stationery was hand painted and then scanned in and photoshopped to remove any shadows. I chose to watercolour with browns, purples and some blues to add depth and keep the colour palette consistent. I wanted the watercolour design to look as though it was a mix of paint and coffee spilling out over the page.\r\n\r\nI used this watercolour design on each piece of stationery to keep consistency and an element of fun. I created each piece of stationery using Adobe Illustrator. Once I had finished each piece, I printed them out. I hand-folded and glued the envelope together so it was usable. I made the inside of the envelope a full watercolour design.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BusinessCard.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/BusinessCard.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Business Card\" width=\"253\" height=\"145\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-2.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-2.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Business Card\" width=\"253\" height=\"145\" /> </a>\r\n<h2>Advert</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert.png 612w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Advert-232x300.png 232w\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Advert\" width=\"612\" height=\"792\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe advert created is a 8.5X11\" poster printed on card stock. I created the design for this poster on Adobe InDesign. I found the image of the paint roller on a free stock-image website. I came up with the message \"Come. Create. Caffeinate.\" as a simple but effective message to explain what Espress Yourself offers. I added the coffee ring at the bottom because I felt as though the paint roller was not sending the full message visually.\r\n<h2>Landing Page</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE.png 391w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/SMALLPAGE-165x300.png 165w\" alt=\"Espress Yourself - Landing Page\" width=\"391\" height=\"709\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThis landing page for Espress Yourself was designed to motivate the customer to submit their email address and sign up to book their wall space to create on. I wanted to keep the design minimal with a lot of white space. I used images revolving around paint and coffee to keep the landing page on brand. I used the dark brown and bright purple colours for consistency. This landing page consists of a form at the top, the benefits and features section, the testimonial section, and a second call to action at the bottom along with the logo and social media links.', 'Visual Identity Project', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-13 16:46:47', '2018-12-13 21:46:47', '', 9, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/12/13/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(270, 1, '2018-12-13 16:47:02', '2018-12-13 21:47:02', '<h1>Re-Branding Project: True Blue Pet Supplies</h1>\r\nWe were asked to choose a local company and rebrand them. We needed to change or update the logo, the stationery, the packaging and all of the marketing strategies. I chose True Blue Pet Supplies located in Campbell River, B.C. As shown below, their logo needed an update and a bump into the 21st century.\r\n<h2>The New Logo</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Primary Logo\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe logo that I created for True Blue Pet Supplies is a clean, modern, circular design. The round, organic design reflects the organic nature of Vancouver Island and True Blue as a company. The fact that their products are all natural is complimented by the natural feel of this logo design.\r\nThe main pop of colour I chose for the logo is a natural blue-green colour that provides the bright element of visual interest. This tone of blue is calm and breezy, while making the logo easy to read on stationery, invoices, etc. This colour is much more modern and clean than the stark \"Windows Paint Program\" shade of blue that was originally used.\r\n<h2>The Old Logo</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/1.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/1.jpg\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/1.jpg 640w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/1-300x164.jpg 300w\" alt=\"True Blue Store Front\" width=\"640\" height=\"350\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/download.jpeg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/download.jpeg\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"True Blue Present Day\" width=\"298\" height=\"169\" /> </a>\r\n<h2>Logo Variations &amp; Patterns</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-6.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"260cd08\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-6.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-6.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-6-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-6-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-6-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Secondary Logo\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /></a></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"260cd08\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Paw Print\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /></a></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-5.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"260cd08\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-5.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-5.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-5-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-5-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-5-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Logo Variation\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /></a></figure>\r\nFrom left to right: The secondary logo, the monogram and the wordmark.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-1.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-1.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-1.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-1-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-1-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-1-1-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Icon - Blue\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-1.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-1.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-1.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-1-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-1-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-2-1-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Icon - Yellow\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-1.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-1.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-1.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-1-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-1-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-1-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Icon - Green\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-4.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-4.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-4.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-4-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-4-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-4-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Icon - Light Blue\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nSeen above: The icons.\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"a5cd5cf\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Artboard-3-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Cat Pattern\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /></a></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dogpatternblue.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"a5cd5cf\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dogpatternblue.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dogpatternblue.png 360w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dogpatternblue-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dogpatternblue-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dogpatternblue-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Dog Pattern\" width=\"360\" height=\"360\" /></a></figure>\r\nThe patterns that I created for True Blue are very simple and whimsical line drawings of dogs, cats, bones, toy balls and leaves. These patterns are to be used on certain packaging and collateral branding elements. The colours used in these patterns stay true to the colour palette chosen for the company and ties in their love of animals with the fun animal prints.\r\n<h2>Stationery</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Colorful-Business-Card-MockUp.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Colorful-Business-Card-MockUp.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Colorful-Business-Card-MockUp.png 2300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Colorful-Business-Card-MockUp-300x215.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Colorful-Business-Card-MockUp-768x551.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Colorful-Business-Card-MockUp-1024x735.png 1024w\" alt=\"True Blue Business Card Mockup\" width=\"2300\" height=\"1650\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nBecause of the simple and modern look of the branding, I want the stationery to accent the whimsical and playful side of the True Blue company. All of the stationery will be printed on recycled paper to keep the business sustainable and eco-friendly.\r\n\r\nThe business cards will be bright and fun. There are two versions of the chosen design: the first has the top of the business card as the brand’s yellow colour with the white paw print logo and the back of the card has the darker blue colour with the information in the off-white ivory colour; the second version has the green colour with the “True” [paw-print] “Blue” logo as the top of the business card and the lighter blue colour on the back side with the information. The business cards will be printed on a recycled cold-pressed watercolour paper that is thick (350-400 GSM), matte and textured.\r\n\r\nThe letterhead will be printed on a recycled A4 paper that is 80 GSM. The paper will be the off-white ivory colour chosen for the brand. There will be the company’s icon printed on the page like a watermark so that writing on top of it will be easily legible. True Blue’s primary logo will be centred at the top of the page, while the company’s information will be posted along the bottom of the page under a line that is the darker blue company colour. The font used on the letterheads will be Shree Devanagari 714, as it is a more familiar font and is easier to read as a big block of text.\r\n\r\nThe envelopes will be a standard #9 or #10 basic white recycled envelope that is 90-100 GSM to hold up during shipping. On the back of the envelope, the “True” [paw-print] “Blue” logo will be centred just under the flap that seals the envelope. The flap will have the paw print pattern design on the outside, and the inside of the flap will have the company’s main logo colour which is the darker blue.\r\n<h2>Packaging</h2>\r\nThe products that I created packaging for are the bulk treats that True Blue Pet Supplies has to offer their clientele and a subscription box that would contain a various selection of treats as well as a toy for the pet and an accessory such as a new collar or a leash. Because of the fun colour palette, the animal friendly and whimsical patterns and the sustainability, this product packaging fits within the True Blue brand.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BagMockups.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BagMockups.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BagMockups.png 2500w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BagMockups-300x132.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BagMockups-768x339.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BagMockups-1024x451.png 1024w\" alt=\"True Blue Bulk Bag Mockups\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1102\" /> </a>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BabyBlueBagMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"180e3eb\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BabyBlueBagMockup-1024x768.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BabyBlueBagMockup-1024x768.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BabyBlueBagMockup-300x225.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BabyBlueBagMockup-768x576.png 768w\" alt=\"True Blue Bulk Bag Mockup - Light Blue\" width=\"525\" height=\"394\" /></a></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_GreenBagMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"180e3eb\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_GreenBagMockup-1024x768.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_GreenBagMockup-1024x768.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_GreenBagMockup-300x225.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_GreenBagMockup-768x576.png 768w\" alt=\"True Blue Bulk Bag Mockup - Green\" width=\"525\" height=\"394\" /></a></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BlueBagMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"180e3eb\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BlueBagMockup-1024x768.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BlueBagMockup-1024x768.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BlueBagMockup-300x225.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_BlueBagMockup-768x576.png 768w\" alt=\"True Blue Bulk Bag Mockup - Blue\" width=\"525\" height=\"394\" /></a></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"gallery-item\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_YellowBagMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\"180e3eb\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_YellowBagMockup-1024x768.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_YellowBagMockup-1024x768.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_YellowBagMockup-300x225.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_YellowBagMockup-768x576.png 768w\" alt=\"True Blue Bulk Bag Mockup - Yellow\" width=\"525\" height=\"394\" /></a></figure>\r\nI created a recyclable paper soft-pouch bag for the bulk treats. This bag is resealable. I have created two designs for this packaging. They each have a similar concept, and are quite simple packaging. There will be different colours for each bag, depending on size and I hope that the customer will choose whatever colour appeals to them regardless. The bags will be a single colour, with an off-white ivory coloured block in the centre of the front and back which contains the logo and information about the company and the treats inside such as the weight (ex. 250 grams), a recyclable sign, a bit of the company story, nutrition facts and where the treats were manufactured and the address and phone number of True Blue in Campbell River. The inside of the bags will not be printed on, but will be coated with a wax- coating that will break down once recycled.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxOutside.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxOutside-1024x1024.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxOutside-1024x1024.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxOutside-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxOutside-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxOutside-768x768.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxOutside-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Subscription Box Mockup - Dog Pattern\" width=\"525\" height=\"525\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxInside.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxInside-1024x1024.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxInside-1024x1024.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxInside-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxInside-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxInside-768x768.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_DogBoxInside-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Subscription Box Mockup - Dog Pattern\" width=\"525\" height=\"525\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxInside.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxInside-1024x1024.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxInside-1024x1024.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxInside-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxInside-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxInside-768x768.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxInside-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Subscription Box Mockup - Cat Pattern\" width=\"525\" height=\"525\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxOutside.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxOutside-1024x1024.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxOutside-1024x1024.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxOutside-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxOutside-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxOutside-768x768.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week9_CatBoxOutside-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Subscription Box Mockup - Cat Pattern\" width=\"525\" height=\"525\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe subscription box I created is a recyclable one-piece cardboard box that is printed with the True Blue dog or cat pattern on the outside with a glossy finish. The top of the box will have the company logo enclosed in an off-white ivory box for legibility. The inside of the subscription box is the True Blue darker turquoise blue colour with the True Blue reversed paw print logo. The box will contain a variety of supplies curated in store for the customer’s pet: a branded bulk bag containing a selection of treats, a toy for the pet and an accessory such as a new collar or a leash. The box will also contain a branded sticker, which they can put on their car, phone, laptop, etc. This will help with advertisement and marketing. The products will be wrapped in tissue paper matching the colour of the box. On top of the wrapping paper, there will be a postcard/notecard that will have the company logo, an introduction to the monthly box and a quote about pets on the front and a description of each product in the box on the back. Customers will have the option to buy these boxes once or have a monthly subscription which can be shipped to them or can be picked up in-store.\r\n\r\nPutting myself in the shoes of the customer aided me in arriving at the final packaging concepts. An average paper bulk bag is not memorable and is usually just tossed into the garbage. I want the customer to enjoy the process of picking out the treats and have the bags be memorable and bring them a personal joy. The bright and fun packaging will draw the customer into the product. Subscription boxes are becoming more and more popular due to the ease of having something sent to your house and knowing that you will be sent quality products. The subscription box also gives the customer a chance to try something new and different.\r\n<h2>Social Media</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup.png 4167w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup-768x768.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup-1024x1024.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramMockup-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"True Blue Social Media - Instagram Mockup\" width=\"4167\" height=\"4167\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramProfileMockup.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramProfileMockup.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramProfileMockup.png 2938w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramProfileMockup-300x200.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramProfileMockup-768x512.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_InstagramProfileMockup-1024x683.png 1024w\" alt=\"True Blue Social Media - Instagram Mockup\" width=\"2938\" height=\"1959\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe company needs more of an online presence. Instagram would give True Blue the option to post pictures of their products, their customers’ pets and some of their subscription box options to give people a taste of what they could be getting with their subscription. To get in touch with the younger generation, Instagram is a great option. Customers would be able to see the company in a new, modern light and it could bring attention to their brand over big-box companies who do not have the local values that True Blue has.\r\n<h2>Marketing</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Billboard.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Billboard.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Billboard.png 2167w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Billboard-300x210.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Billboard-768x538.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Billboard-1024x717.png 1024w\" alt=\"True Blue Marketing - Bus Stop Billboard\" width=\"2167\" height=\"1517\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nBecause Campbell River is a smaller city, bus stop billboards are an expected and familiar form of advertising. To market the True Blue company in a simple but funny way would draw the eye to the advertistment. The “No Butts About It” slogan is a memorable yet effective play on words and helps get the message across that True Blue has the best products you can offer to your pet. I see these advertisements as a series using different animals and the same slogans.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Crosswalk.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Crosswalk.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Crosswalk.png 1707w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Crosswalk-300x225.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Crosswalk-768x576.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/AlyssaWillis_Week10_Crosswalk-1024x768.png 1024w\" alt=\"True Blue Marketing - Crosswalk\" width=\"1707\" height=\"1280\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe crosswalk or zebra crossing option of marketing/advertising is a different, but powerful option. The idea is to put the True Blue paw print logo, along with some of the company blue paw prints across the white bands of a few crosswalks. Being a pet supplies company, the target audience are pet owners or future pet owners and most of those people will most likely be active and out walking their pets. I believe this would bring recognition to the brand in a new and exciting way that most people in Campbell River haven’t seen.\r\n<h2>Collateral Branding</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Facade_1.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Facade_1.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Facade_1.png 2000w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Facade_1-300x225.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Facade_1-768x576.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Facade_1-1024x768.png 1024w\" alt=\"True Blue Collateral Branding - Storefront\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" /> </a>\r\nThe storefront design that I created is an inviting, colourful and playful design that would draw customers into the store. The company name is placed above the storefront so it can be seen from a distance. The company logo is also on the door so anyone walking by can see it clearly as well.\r\nI added paw prints on the windows as a playful touch. The awning is printed with the dog pattern created for the company and is the company’s blue colour. I created the awning this way to keep the inviting and playful feel of the company.\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteDog.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteDog-1024x918.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteDog-1024x918.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteDog-300x269.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteDog-768x689.png 768w\" alt=\"True Blue Collateral Branding - Tote Bag Dog Pattern\" width=\"525\" height=\"471\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteCat.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteCat-1024x918.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteCat-1024x918.png 1024w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteCat-300x269.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/ToteCat-768x689.png 768w\" alt=\"True Blue Collateral Branding - Tote Bag Cat Pattern\" width=\"525\" height=\"471\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe tote bags are a key component of True Blue’s stance on recycling and the environment. I think they are incredibly important to this brand’s marketing and branding. There is the cat bag and the dog bag - similar to the subscription boxes. Having recyclable tote bags is an important option for a store to have especially a store that cares so deeply for pets and wildlife. The playful and whimsical patterns are a great incentive to help the customer lower their plastic use. Also, this could be a great gift giving incentive as well; customers could fill the bag with a few items and gift it to a friend.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Candle.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Candle.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Candle.png 4500w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Candle-300x210.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Candle-768x538.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Candle-1024x717.png 1024w\" alt=\"True Blue Collateral Branding - Candle\" width=\"4500\" height=\"3150\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nBecause having a pet is not always the best smelling endeavour, I created the True Blue candles. There are two candles: one directed towards cat lovers and one directed towards dog lovers. I think these would be a great gift giving incentive to the customer as well as something a customer would love to have in their own home. The “Nix The Litter” candle, directed toward cat owners, is a playful way of saying “This candle will hide that terrible cat litter smell that your lovely furry friend leaves behind.” The “Tall Tails” candle is directed towards dog owners and can help hide the smell of your wonderful four legged friend after they have had an adventure in the rain.', 'Re-Branding Project', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-13 16:47:02', '2018-12-13 21:47:02', '', 11, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/12/13/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(271, 1, '2018-12-13 16:47:16', '2018-12-13 21:47:16', '<h2>Personal Logo</h2>\r\nSince I was young, I have loved art, computers and space. I am enthralled by the way a brush and some colour can change the look and feel of something. I am astounded by the way you can create something from your mind with a little imagination and some supplies. I have been using a computer since the age of 5 and within a few months, I was teaching my parents how to do things on the computer. And I am completely taken aback by the vastness of space, and imagining what could be out there.\r\n\r\nSo, with all these things in mind, a graphic designer seemed like the career that contained the perfect combination of my favourite things and my skill sets. But, where could I introduce some space vibes? Of course, every client wouldn\'t want NASA type logos or galaxy watercolored backgrounds and all that stuff.\r\n\r\nI decided that for my personal logo - I would create a nerdy, spacey, astronaut feel.\r\n\r\nWhy not? It\'s my logo!\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/black-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Black\" width=\"433\" height=\"432\" />\r\n\r\nThis is the basic logo. The logo that would be seen most of the time - you know, when some would say it\'s \"inappropriate\" to have a bright pink logo present. Which is strange... Because pink is a fantastically happy colour.\r\n\r\nI created this logo by finding a NASA-like font and making use of it to reflect me! I brought the letters A and W (no, not like the burgers, but yum!) into Illustrator and modified them until they melded into one another.\r\n\r\nIt\'s funny, it kind of looks the way I sign my initials.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWguides.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWguides.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWguides.png 1208w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWguides-300x221.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWguides-768x565.png 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWguides-1024x753.png 1024w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Black Clearspace\" width=\"1208\" height=\"888\" /> </a>\r\n<h2>Logo Variations</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blue.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blue.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blue.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blue-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blue-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blue-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Blue\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellow.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellow.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellow.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellow-300x296.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellow-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Yellow\" width=\"433\" height=\"427\" /> </a>\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pink.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pink.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pink-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pink-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pink-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Pink\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" />\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/green.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/green.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/green.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/green-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/green-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/green-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Green\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blueoutline.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blueoutline.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blueoutline.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blueoutline-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blueoutline-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blueoutline-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Blue Outline\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellowoutline.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellowoutline.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellowoutline.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellowoutline-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellowoutline-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/yellowoutline-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Yellow Outline\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pinkoutline.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"default\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pinkoutline.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pinkoutline.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pinkoutline-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pinkoutline-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pinkoutline-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Pink Outline\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/greenoutline.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/greenoutline.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/greenoutline.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/greenoutline-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/greenoutline-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/greenoutline-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Green Outline\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThese are all the variations of my personal logo. There is not much difference from the basic logo - but I have always been drawn to bright and vibrant colour. When I became a nail technician, bright colours were my favourite way to express myself. Having a few different colours of this logo makes it flexible. I could use it anywhere, on anything!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWname.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWname.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWname.png 721w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWname-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWname-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/blackWname-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Black Square With Name\" width=\"525\" height=\"525\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/whiteWname.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/whiteWname.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/whiteWname.png 721w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/whiteWname-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/whiteWname-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/whiteWname-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - White Square With Name\" width=\"525\" height=\"525\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThese other logo variations include my name underneath my symbol. I made this version for when I needed a more boxed in version of my logo - and needed my full name front and centre!\r\n<h2>The Process</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/img001.jpg\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/img001.jpg\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/img001.jpg 2483w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/img001-231x300.jpg 231w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/img001-768x998.jpg 768w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/img001-788x1024.jpg 788w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Process Sketches\" width=\"2483\" height=\"3228\" /> </a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/test.png\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\"yes\">\r\n<img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/test.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/test.png 433w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/test-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/test-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/test-100x100.png 100w\" alt=\"Alyssa Willis Logo - Process Illustrator\" width=\"433\" height=\"433\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nI went through a quick but thorough process to create this logo. I really had my mind set on what I wanted to portray in my logo and my brand.', 'Personal Logo', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-13 16:47:16', '2018-12-13 21:47:16', '', 13, 'http://localhost:8888/2018/12/13/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
